 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uzerbit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zerbit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/6/02 9:56:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What Makes A Good Warrior?</span><hr size=1>  A lot of what was mentioned here is great info for grouping. I just wanted to add a little bit about what i do on raids. I found that hotkeys are very useful. I have an assist key for the puller, an assist key for the MA(when i am not MA), and an assist key for the melee officer(in our guild a prancing bard). When we get adds in HoT or other zones the bard will often call out which mob he wants tanked first and so on until a tank is on each unmezzable mob. It helps to be able to select my mob as soon as it is called. In an exp group i switch the bards name with that of the chanter in my group. In some camps a chanter will not be able to mez a certain mob and will call for help. I like to be able to switch to his mob right away. <br>
<br>
 Also on a raid if you are the MA do not be afraid to shout orders at people attacking before you call the mob, or to direct the melee where you want them. For some reason not all melee will just stay opposite you behind a mob. You need to be able to get them there. I also set up a channel with the puller on our raids so he can tell me when to tag and when to wait for an add to move away a bit.<br>
<br>
 Also don't worry that much about the switching out the shield to stun thingy. You are already 46 and if you are grinding xp daily you should be mid 50's soon enough. Once you reach that stage in your warrior life your kick will have aquired the ability to stun and you will not need a shield.<br>
<br>
 Don't pop your disciplines at stupid times. Once you reach 55, if you pop any disc except defensive or evasive you are just showing off. I love equipping tantor's tusk and going berserk just like everyone else. But if you want to be purely efficient then wait until things are really hairy and everyone is convinced death is imminent, then pop defensive and give your cleric time to med one more CH. You will be hailed a hero and a genius and your willpower at not having using fellstrike on Dragoon Zytl 30 minutes earlier will be rewarded !!!<br>
<br>
 Also remember to work well with your other warriors. Aggro switching is a tough thing to learn when you are all doing it for the first time. A lot of other things will eventually come up that will require two or more warriors. If you guys are always competing for gear and hate each other.......well things are not gonna be fun for your guild.<br>
<br>
 Joke, but not too much. Nothing i hate more than someone who doesn't know when it is time to focus. EQ has tons of down time for joking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kudil>Kudil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/7/02 8:44:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What Makes A Good Warrior?</span><hr size=1> Nahh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If you got a whiney enchanter... taunt em of course, but if you have one with a good sense of humor... get em smacked every now and then =P (yes this is joking heh) <p><a target = new href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64016">~Kudil 60 Warrior</a>
