</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucrayno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crayno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 5:59:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What Makes A Good Warrior?</span><hr size=1> Don't be afraid to die/get wiped.<br>
Try mobs that are supposably too strong for you and there can be 3 outcomes:<br>
-You will get your asses handed severely<br>
-You will actually get close to killing it<br>
-Against all expectations you will win!<br>
In the first 2 cases you will most likely learn a lot and kill him in the (near or far)future<br>
In the latter case you will get a morale boost that can last a long time<br>
<br>
Don't whine for buffs 1 second after it wears off,a good player knows when his/her buffs wear off.<br>
Have knowledge or obtain it on wich mobs need Glamour of Kintaz/Rapture and wich needs regular mez.<br>
Pay attention wich mob is mezzed when and with wich spell.<br>
Kill healers/casters first when you're without a Chanter and kill melees first if you have one.<br>
Don't be afraid to ask questions,even a level 60 player with 100+AA points doesn't know everything. <p>
