</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umowgley.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mowgley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/16/02 10:53:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What Makes A Good Warrior?</span><hr size=1> Reputation above all.<br>
<br>
Gear comes in time to anyone.  (yes iksar can wear plate class armor from luclin or velious, at least most of it)<br>
<br>
Tactics can be learned the hard way or the easy way.  Having learned the hard way, I make less mistakes now than when I started..by far.<br>
<br>
When I shout and people I have grouped with are in the zone, I get tells, &quot;sorry we are full, but if we have an opening you are it&quot; or &quot;come to (fill in the blank) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  &quot;<br>
<br>
I am not the top level tank in the game, but I can be fun to group with and listen well to those that know more.  Paying attention does more to endear you to other players than any other action in the game.  Consideration for Mana and casters getting loot seems to be so often left out that I wonder why we dont have open bloodshed all the time between classes sometimes.<br>
<br>
Tip the cleric, Tip the chanter, make sure the casters are also getting loot.  Dont be greedy, carry plat for ports or peris, carry sow/invis potions.  Get an EB item.<br>
<br>
It adds up, considerate players often do well in enhancing their rep.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion <p>-Strongtooth, 50 Iksar Warrior<BR>
